definitions.definition: Serving as commander or member of a body of detached light troops .
Adherent to a party or faction ; especially, having the character of blind, passionate, or unreasonable adherence to a party.
examples: They were blinded by partisan zeal.

definitions.definition: Devoted to or biased in support of a party, group, or cause.
